solutions.content:
**Addition Operation**

Straight-forward solution where you add up the bits one at a time.

```
public class Solution {
    public string AddBinary(string a, string b) {
        var n1 = a.Length - 1;
        var n2 = b.Length - 1;
        var carry = 0;

        var result = new StringBuilder();
        while(carry > 0 || n1 >= 0 || n2 >= 0) {
            var c1 = n1 >= 0 ? a[n1] : '0';
            var c2 = n2 >= 0 ? b[n2] : '0';

            var sum = carry + (c1-'0') + (c2-'0');
            if(sum > 1) {
                carry = 1;
                sum = sum - 2;
            } else {
                carry = 0;
            }

            result.Insert(0, sum);

            n1--;
            n2--;
        }

        return result.ToString();
    }
}
```

**Bit Manipulation**

A follow-up to this question is to solve this problem without using addition operation. We can use bit manipulation instead. The intuition is that to calculate carry, at least 2 of the 3 bits (carry, bit from string a, bit from string b) have to be 1. Therefore, you can do:
`carry = (c1 | carry ) & (c2 | carry) & (c1 | c2);`

```
public class Solution {
    public string AddBinary(string a, string b) {
        var n1 = a.Length - 1;
        var n2 = b.Length - 1;
        var carry = 0;

        var result = new StringBuilder();
        while(carry > 0 || n1 >= 0 || n2 >= 0) {
            var c1 = n1 >= 0 ? a[n1] - '0' : 0;
            var c2 = n2 >= 0 ? b[n2] - '0' : 0;

            var sum = (c1 ^ c2 ^ carry);
            carry = (c1 | carry ) & (c2 | carry) & (c1 | c2);

            result.Insert(0, sum);

            n1--;
            n2--;
        }

        return result.ToString();
    }
}

```

